			<abstract>
				<p>Statement of Erna Meyer about the murder of her brother Alfred, a dentist who was harassed by a leading Nazi, also a dentist, even
					before 1933. In 1933 the brother voluntarily went into police custody for a few weeks as persecution got worse. He then left to
					work in a nearby town but on May 16, 1933 was picked up by the Nazi and his friends (all named). Several days later his dead body
					was found.</p>
			</abstract>
