	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1" facs="EHRI-ET-WL16560946_01.jpg"/>
			<p>PIIc No 946 (EW1 783-787)</p>
			<p>Statement regarding the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">murder</term> of her <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">brother</term> , Dr <persName
					ref="https://yvng.yadvashem.org/nameDetails.html?itemId=1531201" type="victim">Alfred Meyer</persName> of <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/2952539/barmen.html">Barmen-Düsseldorf</placeName>, on <date when="1933-05-16">16 May 1933</date></p>
			<pb n="3" facs="EHRI-ET-WL16560946_03.jpg"/>
			<p>I, the undersigned</p>
			<p><persName ref="#ehri_et_meyer_niedermann_erna">Erna Meyer</persName></p>
			<p>hereby swear by this affidavit that the following statement is the truth. I am fully aware that this statement is to be used by a
					<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2658434/switzerland.html">Swiss</placeName>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1127" type="subject">law court</term> and I am aware that those who
				swear a false affidavit, either deliberately or inadvertently, are subject to severe penalties under the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-950" type="subject">criminal law</term> of all countries including
					<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2658434/switzerland.html">Switzerland</placeName> and <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/6254930/palestine.html">Palestine</placeName>. For this reason, and of course as a matter of morality
				which requires me to tell the truth and nothing but the truth, I have considered every word that I have written and fully guarantee
				the truth of this affidavit.</p>
			<p>I had a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">brother</term>, Dr <persName
					ref="https://yvng.yadvashem.org/nameDetails.html?itemId=1531201" type="victim">Alfred Meyer</persName>, who was born on <date
					when="1989-03-24">24 March 1898</date>. He left grammar <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1134"
					type="subject">school</term> even before the age of seventeen to join the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1076" type="subject">army</term> as a volunteer; in <date when="1915-02"
					>February 1915</date> he marched into <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1441" type="subject"
					>battle</term> and was a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1097" type="subject">soldier</term> until
				the end of the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1080" type="subject">war</term>. He was <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-791" type="subject">wounded</term> no less than three times but
				nevertheless went back to the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1441" type="subject">battlefield</term>
				each time, was awarded the <foreign xml:lang="de"><term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1093" type="subject"
						>Bayrische Verdienstkreuz</term></foreign> and the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1093"
					type="subject">Iron Cross Second Class</term>, and was promoted to <foreign xml:lang="de">Vizewachtmeister</foreign>. On returning
				from the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1080" type="subject">war</term> he completed his <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-842" type="subject">education</term>, first at <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1134" type="subject">school</term> where he passed the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-842" type="subject">Abitur</term>; he then studied <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-285" type="subject">dentistry</term> and set up in practice as a <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-285" type="subject">dentist</term> in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/2952539/barmen.html">Wuppertal-Barmen</placeName>. He had never been active <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-947" type="subject">politically</term>, either before or after this; in
				particular, he had never been a member of the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-982" type="subject"
					>Socialist</term> or <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-971" type="subject">Communist Parties</term>,
				nor had he ever done anything for any of these <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-958" type="subject"
					>parties</term>. Even before the revolution of <date when="1933">1933</date> he knew that there was a certain antipathy towards
				him in <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-360" type="subject">National Socialist</term> circles in
					<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2952539/barmen.html">Barmen</placeName>; he attributed this to the fact not only that he
				was a Jew, but also that one of the leading <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-360" type="subject">National
					Socialists</term> of <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2952539/barmen.html">Barmen</placeName>, a <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-285" type="subject">dentist</term> named <persName ref="#ehri_et_viering"
					>Viering</persName>, had had his practice opposite my <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822"
					type="subject">brother’s</term> for some time, and as my <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822"
					type="subject">brother</term> was very popular with his patients he <persName ref="#ehri_et_viering">Viering</persName> found it
				difficult to get a practice.</p>
			<p>This <persName ref="#ehri_et_viering">Viering</persName> had been sued for libel even before the revolution of <date when="1933"
					>1933</date> because he had stated that my <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject"
					>brother</term> was suffering from a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-292" type="subject">sexually
					transmitted disease</term>. My <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">brother</term>
				underwent a very thorough examination proving that this accusation was completely false. Consequently, <persName
					ref="#ehri_et_viering">Viering</persName> was punished. <persName ref="#ehri_et_viering">Viering</persName> tried another libel,
				saying that my <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">brother</term>, in his capacity as a
				certifying <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-285" type="subject">doctor</term>, had produced false
				certificates for patients to claim on national <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-791" type="subject"
					>health</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-941" type="subject">insurance</term>. Again, this accusation was proved
				to be unfounded after the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-285" type="subject">dentists’</term>
				<pb n="4" facs="EHRI-ET-WL16560946_04.jpg"/> professional body had thoroughly examined the case and found my <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">brother</term> to be blameless.</p>
			<p>After the beginning of the revolution my <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject"
					>brother’s</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">house</term> was immediately <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1135" type="subject">searched</term> but nothing was found which might be
				used against him in some way. These searches were mainly carried out by the following <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-360" type="subject">National Socialists</term>: <persName
					ref="#ehri_et_fischer">Fischer</persName>, <persName ref="#ehri_et_viering">Viering</persName>, <persName
					ref="#ehri_et_birkenstock">Birkenstock</persName> and <persName ref="#ehri_et_noelle">Noelle</persName>. These <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1135" type="subject">searches</term> took place at a time when my <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">brother</term> was travelling abroad trying to
				discover whether there was a possibility for him to <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-203" type="subject"
					>emigrate</term>. My <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">brother</term> then
				returned and even went back to <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2952539/barmen.html">Barmen</placeName> despite several
				warnings, because he was of the opinion that he was an honest and upright <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">man</term>, and that running away would be the action
				of a coward.</p>
			<p>Whilst he was in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2952539/barmen.html">Barmen</placeName> he felt so <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-641" type="subject">persecuted</term> that one night he did not sleep at
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">home</term> but instead at a friend’s. During
				the night his <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">house</term> was <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1135" type="subject">searched</term> again. This <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1135" type="subject">search</term> was conducted in such a way that damage
				to the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-945" type="subject">property</term> was clearly intended. The
				next day my <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">brother</term> went to the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1119" type="subject">police</term> and asked to be kept in so-called
				voluntary <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-620" type="subject">protective custody</term> because he <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-829" type="subject">feared</term> for his life. The <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1119" type="subject">police</term> did as he asked and so he spent the
				time from the end of March until <date when="1933-05-10">10 May</date> in <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-620" type="subject">protective custody</term>.</p>
			<p>I must state, however, that his voluntary stay in <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-620" type="subject"
					>protective custody</term> became involuntary during this time because an <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1135" type="subject">investigation</term> was started against him, for
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-649" type="subject">political</term> reasons. This <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1135" type="subject">investigation</term> was extremely hard for him,
				mainly because he tried desperately for five weeks to have his first <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-634" type="subject">interrogation</term>, which in the end was only
				brought about by friends, including non-Jewish friends, who finally convinced the authorities to carry out an <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-634" type="subject">interrogation</term>.</p>
			<p>The <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1135" type="subject">investigation</term> did not bring anything to
				light since, as already mentioned, there was nothing that could come to light, and so he was <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-619" type="subject">released</term> on <date when="1933-05-10">10 May
					1933</date>. In the night after his <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-619" type="subject"
					>release</term> his <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">house</term> was <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1135" type="subject">searched</term> again; he was not at <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">home</term> because he had preferred to spend the
				night at the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">house</term> of a <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-724" type="subject">Christian</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-819" type="subject">family</term> he was friendly with. On that occasion
				his <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">flat</term> was devastated, all kinds of
				valuables like record players and records were <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-356" type="subject"
					>destroyed</term>, carpets were slashed, lamps were broken, the fully fitted kitchen was torn out. Many valuable goods were
				stolen, and they even went so far as to take away his <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-836"
					type="subject">suits</term> and <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-836" type="subject"
				>shoes</term>.</p>
			<p>After this occurrence my <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">brother</term> preferred to
				leave <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2952539/barmen.html">Barmen</placeName> and after spending some days somewhere else <pb
					n="5" facs="EHRI-ET-WL16560946_05.jpg"/> he started <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-943"
					type="subject">work</term> as a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-285" type="subject">dentist</term>
				in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2934246/duesseldorf.html">Düsseldorf</placeName> whilst preparing to <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-203" type="subject">emigrate</term>. His <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">wife</term>, also a <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-285" type="subject">dentist</term>, had a practice in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/2934246/duesseldorf.html">Düsseldorf</placeName> and the two decided to stand in for each other until
				they could <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-203" type="subject">emigrate</term>, as having only a little
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-934" type="subject">money</term> they could not do without an
				income.</p>
			<p>On <date when="1933-05-16">16 May</date> the telephone rang in his practice in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/2934246/duesseldorf.html">Düsseldorf</placeName>. It was <persName ref="#ehri_et_noelle"
					>Noelle</persName> – already mentioned above – who asked whether my <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">brother</term> was there and when the answer was
					<q>yes</q> he said, <q>thats</q> all I want to know’ and rang off. In the afternoon he rang again and soon after the call my <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">brother</term> left the practice and went to a <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-819" type="subject">family</term> he was friendly with. In the street he
				was followed and soon after he had arrived a car stopped in which there were five <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1207" type="subject">people</term>, among them the four mentioned above,
				who had taken part in the previous <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1135" type="subject"
				>searches</term>.</p>
			<p><persName ref="#ehri_et_viering">Viering</persName> stayed at the wheel, the four others went into the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">flat</term>, threw my <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">brother</term> onto the floor, tied him up and dragged
				him into the car. The other <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1207" type="subject">people</term> present
				were also tied up, and as one of them had tried to get to the telephone to call for help before being tied up, the telephone was
				destroyed, to make any communication with the outside world impossible.</p>
			<p>The <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1136" type="subject">registration</term> number had been noted by
				several <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1207" type="subject">people</term> but the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1135" type="subject">investigation</term> showed that it was false. The
				help the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1119" type="subject">police</term> gave us was just a formality
				with no practical and effective support at all, and so we were not able to discover his whereabouts.</p>
			<p>At first we had engaged the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-360" type="subject">National Socialist</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-899" type="subject">lawyer</term>
				<persName ref="#ehri_et_kintzen">KINTZEN</persName> in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2934246/duesseldorf.html"
					>Düsseldorf</placeName>; he, however, later terminated the brief because the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-360" type="subject">Party</term> had advised him not to engage in this
				case – a fact we do know for certain.</p>
			<p>Some days after my <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">brother</term> had disappeared a
				forester informed [us] that at the Bewerdam, between <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2934246/duesseldorf.html"
					>Düsseldorf</placeName> and <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2952539/barmen.html">Barmen</placeName>, the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-515" type="subject">dead body</term> of a <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">man</term> had been washed up. It turned out to be my
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">brother’s</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-515" type="subject">corpse</term>, which had been thrown into the water;
				his head had been stuck into a sack and his feet tied to a copy machine to prevent the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-515" type="subject">body</term> from surfacing. There must have been very
				particular circumstances which allowed the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-515" type="subject"
					>body</term> to come up again nevertheless. We ourselves did not get the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-515" type="subject">body</term> – <pb n="6"
					facs="EHRI-ET-WL16560946_06.jpg"/> on the contrary, it was handed over several days later to the chief <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-735" type="subject">rabbi</term> in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/2934246/duesseldorf.html">Düsseldorf</placeName> who in exchange had strict orders not to show his
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-515" type="subject">corpse</term> to his relatives. Later we learnt
				– not from the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-735" type="subject">rabbi</term> but from others who had
				seen the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-515" type="subject">corpse</term> – that he had been <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-791" type="subject">stabbed</term> in the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-292" type="subject">abdomen</term> and other parts of his body; he had
				been <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">shot</term> in the head twice and his <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-515" type="subject">body</term> had been maltreated and mutilated in a
				disgusting way. The <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1127" type="subject">court</term> refused to deal
				with the case, so the records were sent to <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2950159/berlin.html">Berlin</placeName>, but are
				said to have been lost in transit.</p>
			<p>By order of the authorities the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-805" type="subject">funeral</term> was
				secret and very quiet. Any <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1069" type="subject">newspapers</term> which
				reported the case were <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-584" type="subject">confiscated</term>. We were
				dictated the text of the obituary notice, so we preferred to simply inform <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1207" type="subject">people</term> that he had <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">died</term>.</p>
			<p>I declare again that everything I have described here is the truth and that I have not added or changed anything.</p>
			<p>Signed <persName ref="#ehri_et_meyer_niedermann_erna">Erna Meyer</persName></p>
